12/05/2010
SYDNEY, Australia -- Federal police arrested war crimes suspect Dragan Vasiljkovic, who had been on the run since the end of March. Officials say he was arrested just before 5pm local time Wednesday (May 12th) at an undisclosed location He disappeared shortly after the Australian High Court approved his extradition to Croatia. Zagreb says Vasiljkovic, known as "Captain Dragan", was involved in the 1991 torture and killing of Croatian civilians and prisoners of war in the rebel Serb stronghold of Knin, and in the southern village of Bruska in 1993. (ABC, The Australian, Fena, HRT - 12/05/10)
